## Vercel Web Analytics Implementation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for this HTML5 project.

### What Was Implemented

1. **Package Installation**
   - Installed `@vercel/analytics` version 2.0.1 using npm
   - Package added to dependencies in package.json

2. **Analytics Integration**
   - Added Vercel Web Analytics script to `index.html`
   - Implemented the recommended HTML5 integration pattern from official Vercel documentation
   - Used the CDN-based approach with queue initialization for optimal performance

3. **Implementation Details**
   - Added the `window.va` initialization function to queue analytics events before the script loads
   - Included the analytics script from `https://cdn.vercel-insights.com/v1/script.js` with `defer` attribute
   - Placed scripts in the `<head>` section following the existing Speed Insights pattern

### Files Modified

- **frontend/index.html** - Added Vercel Web Analytics script integration
- **frontend/package.json** - Added @vercel/analytics dependency
- **frontend/package-lock.json** - Updated with new dependency lock information

### Implementation Notes

- Followed the official Vercel documentation from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart
- Used the HTML5/vanilla JavaScript implementation pattern as documented
- The project already had `@vercel/speed-insights` configured, so the analytics implementation follows the same pattern
- The `game.html` file was empty (0 bytes), so no changes were made to it
- Analytics will automatically track page views and web vitals once deployed to Vercel

### Verification

- HTML syntax validated successfully
- Node.js environment confirmed working
- Package installation completed without errors
- All dependencies resolved correctly

### Next Steps

When deployed to Vercel:
1. Analytics data will automatically start collecting
2. View analytics in the Vercel dashboard under your project's Analytics tab
3. The analytics will track page views, custom events, and user interactions
